# Basic Router Configuration Lab

## Overview

This lab demonstrates foundational Cisco IOS router configuration tasks performed in Packet Tracer while studying for the CCNA.

Skills demonstrated include:

- IPv4 interface configuration
- Interface descriptions
- Enabling router interfaces
- Connectivity verification
- Configuration saving and management
- Basic troubleshooting



## Topology

![Topology](screenshots/topology.png)



## Addressing Table

| Device | Interface | IP Address |
|---|---|---|
| R1 | G0/0 | 192.168.1.1/24 |
| R1 | G0/1 | 192.168.2.1/24 |
| PC1 | NIC | 192.168.1.10/24 |
| PC2 | NIC | 192.168.2.10/24 |

Default gateways:
- PC1 → 192.168.1.1
- PC2 → 192.168.2.1



## Router Configuration

Configuration file:

- [R1-config.txt](configs/R1-config.txt)

Example interface configuration:


interface GigabitEthernet0/0
 description Link to PC1 LAN
 ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown




